Unique. Only usable if playing for ante.
X is the number of Methuselahs in the game. Put this card in play. When any Methuselah's prey is ousted, the surviving Methuselah wins his or her prey's ante and antes 1 additional card.
{Added to the V:EKN banned list on the 9th of January, 1995.}

Requires a justicar or Inner Circle member.
Choose a non-Camarilla vampire with capacity 5 or less. If this acting vampire is a member of the Inner Circle, you can choose any non-Camarilla vampire instead. Successful referendum means the chosen vampire is burned.
{Added to the V:EKN banned list on the 1st of January, 2008.}

Unique location.
Lock during your unlock phase to trade with a Methuselah who agrees to trade. You can trade pool and cards from your hand and cards you control. The trade cannot result in either Methuselah have less cards in hand than his or her hand size. Any additional terms can be established, but none are enforced by the rules.
{Added to the V:EKN banned list on the 1st of January, 2005.}

Requires a ready justicar. Only one Temptation of Greater Power can be played in a game.
Choose any vampire. Each Methuselah can bid pool for control of that vampire. The highest bid goes to the blood bank; that bidder then steals the vampire. Each Methuselah can be credited up to 5 pool on the bid: winner pays 1 pool toward his or her debt during his or her discard phase until the debt is repaid.
{Added to the V:EKN banned list on the 16th of February, 2016.}
